      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The 2016 Permanent Court of Arbitration (PCA) ruling found that China's claims to historic rights under the 'nine-dash line' were inconsistent with the United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea (UNCLOS). This ruling weakening China's expansive claims, which had not been recognized by all involved states. However, not all countries accept the ruling, and China does not recognize its binding effect. Therefore, from an international legal perspective, some parties believe that the ruling helps clarify the legitimacy of the claims, but it remains a nuanced and contentious issue with ongoing geopolitical implications.",
